Package org.eng.aisp.segmented

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ISegmentedLabeledDataWindow<DATA,LDW extends ILabeledDataWindow<DATA>>
    Design for for labeled data window that has labeled and tagged segments defined over it.
    ISegmentedLabeledDoubleWindow<LDW extends ILabeledDataWindow<double[]>>
    Extends the super-interface simply to define the type of data as an array of doubles.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractSegmentedLabeledDataWindow<DATA,LDW extends ILabeledDataWindow<DATA>>
    Initial implementation of a labeled data window that has labeled and tagged segments defined over it.
    AbstractSegmentedLabeledDoubleWindow<LDW extends ILabeledDataWindow<double[]>>
    Extends the super class just to define the data in the labeled data window as an array of double.
    LabeledSegmentSpec
    Contains the data defining the labels and tags for segment of sound.
    LabelSequence
    Represents a series of labeled time ranges.
    SegmentedSoundRecording
    Extends the super class to define the type of labeled data windows as a SoundRecording.
    SegmentingSoundRecordingShuffleIterable
    A shuffleable iterable producing SoundRecordings from segments defined in an iterable of SegmentedSoundRecordings.
    SoundSegmenter
    Provides the functionality to apply a LabeledSegmentSpec to a SoundRecording or SoundClip.
